blog.name: lunalockes
blog.title: Lunalockes!
blog.description: This is where I'll be updating people on my Nuzlocke playthroughs! I'll be playing as the female character each time (cause I grew up always playing the male character), and will name myself Luna - thus, Lunalockes!

summary: SS Nuzlocke Rules!
title: SS Nuzlocke Rules!
body:
1.       I can only catch the first Pokémon I see on each route. If it faints or flees, I get no second chances.

(Note: This rule only takes place once I can get PokeBalls)

2.       If a Pokémon faints, I will consider it dead, and I will release it the next chance I get. If I black/white out at any point, it’s game over. No resets.

Optional Clauses I’ll Be Using! 

3.       If I have already caught the first Pokémon on the route, I may catch the next one I see. I can do this up to three times before I must capture the third repeat Pokémon, or not catch any Pokémon for the route.

4.       If one of my Pokémon are critically hit at full HP and drop all the way to zero HP, I can revive them ONCE.

5.       If I encounter a shiny Pokémon, I may catch it, regardless of whether or not I have already caught a Pokémon on the route.

6.       I will have my battle style on “Set” to create a harder challenge.

7.       The “First Encounter” rule will be modified for the Safari Zone. I may catch one Pokémon per area in the Safari Zone.

8.       If one of the first encounters is a male Combee, I can catch it and search for a female Combee to replace it.

9.       I cannot use evasion-raising or accuracy-lowering moves.
